This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category because it discusses a stochastic, zero-input Hopfield network. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category because it studies the convergence properties of the network. Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the network to imaging, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of quantum annealing suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
